eate a public ObjectImporterTest.java and might package it with javassist.javassist. \\n\\nImplementing a minimal HTTP server involves a ServerSocket loop that needs to be closed. Since ObjectImporter uses a blocking socket, the server must accept multiple requests, so I could use an ExecutorService to manage this.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Structuring HTTP responses**\\n\\nI need to output the HTTP response header as \\\"HTTP/1.0 200 OK\\\\r\\\\n\\\\r\\\\n\\\". Then I'll use ObjectOutputStream to write the lookup details, like writeInt(id) and writeUTF(classname). \\n\\nFor the call, I'll read the int values for objectId and methodId, along with the number of objects, which includes RemoteRef and String. The response should return a boolean true and writeObject with the result. I’m wondering if I need to drain anything here. This is coming together!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering code options**\\n\\nI’m thinking I might need to use AssertJ to catch throwable exceptions, perhaps calling assertThat. I wonder if I need to find more sources, but maybe the ObjectNotFound isn't necessary. Additionally, I'm realizing I need to write some files and maybe include a license header in them. It seems like keeping everything organized is key here, but I'm still figuring out the best approach to make it all work smoothly.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_HhZ9IbIuio4oEkhfV5IwPLjr|fc_0be0302bd73650260169f9d23f2790819d9266302e7d51fbf2", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/javassist/javassist/3.12.0.GA/src/test/java/javassist/javassist/ObjectImporterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage javassist.javassist;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.BufferedInputStream;\nimport java.io.BufferedOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.InputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.io.OutputStream;\nimport java.net.ServerSocket;\nimport java.net.Socket;\nimport java.net.SocketTimeoutException;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.concurrent.BlockingQueue;\nimport java.util.concurrent.ExecutorService;\nimport java.util.concurrent.Executors;\nimport java.util.concurrent.LinkedBlockingQueue;\nimport java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n\nimport javassist.tools.rmi.ObjectImporter;\nimport javassist.tools.rmi.Proxy;\nimport javassist.tools.rmi.RemoteRef;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ObjectImporterTest {\n    @Test\n    void lookupAndCallSerializeParametersAndCreateProxyFromServerResponses() throws Exception {\n        try (FixtureServer server = new FixtureServer()) {\n            AtomicReference<String> lookupName = new AtomicReference<>();\n            AtomicReference<RemoteRef> remoteArgument = new AtomicReference<>();\n            AtomicReference<String> valueArgument = new AtomicReference<>();\n            server.enqueue(exchange -> {\n                try (ObjectInputStream input = exchange.openObjectInputStream()) {\n                    lookupName.set(input.readUTF());\n                }\n                try (ObjectOutputStream output = exchange.openObjectOutputStream()) {\n                    output.writeInt(42);\n                    output.writeUTF(RemoteProxyFixture.class.getName());\n                }\n            });\n            server.enqueue(exchange -> {\n                try (ObjectInputStream input = exchange.openObjectInputStream()) {\n                    assertThat(input.readInt()).isEqualTo(42);\n                    assertThat(input.readInt()).isEqualTo(7);\n                    assertThat(input.readInt()).isEqualTo(2);\n                    remoteArgument.set((RemoteRef) input.readObject());\n                    valueArgument.set((String) input.readObject());\n                }\n                try (ObjectOutputStream output = exchange.openObjectOutputStream()) {\n                    output.writeBoolean(true);\n                    output.writeObject(\"remote result\");\n                }\n            });\n\n            ObjectImporter importer = new ObjectImporter(\"127.0.0.1\", server.getPort());\n            Object lookedUp = importer.lookupObject(\"service-name\");\n            Object result = importer.call(42, 7, new Object[] {lookedUp, \"plain value\"});\n\n            assertThat(lookedUp).isInstanceOf(RemoteProxyFixture.class);\n            assertThat(((RemoteProxyFixture) lookedUp)._getObjectId()).isEqualTo(42);\n            assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"remote result\");\n            assertThat(lookupName.get()).isEqualTo(\"service-name\");\n            assertThat(remoteArgument.get().oid).isEqualTo(42);\n            assertThat(valueArgument.get()).isEqualTo(\"plain value\");\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void callCreatesProxyWhenResultIsRemoteReference() throws Exception {\n        try (FixtureServer server = new FixtureServer()) {\n            server.enqueue(exchange -> {\n                try (ObjectInputStream input = exchange.openObjectInputStream()) {\n                    assertThat(input.readInt()).isEqualTo(11);\n                    assertThat(input.readInt()).isEqualTo(5);\n                    assertThat(input.readInt()).isZero();\n                }\n                try (ObjectOutputStream output = exchange.openObjectOutputStream()) {\n                    output.writeBoolean(true);\n                    output.writeObject(new RemoteRef(84, RemoteProxyFixture.class.getName()));\n                }\n            });\n\n            ObjectImporter importer = new ObjectImporter(\"127.0.0.1\", server.getPort());\n            Object result = importer.call(11, 5, new Object[0]);\n\n            assertThat(result).isInstanceOf(R